parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering column lock can cause the vehicle to become inoperable, making it difficult or impossible to start the vehicle, and potentially leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The steering wheel becomes permanently locked
the vehicle will not start
the "Service Column Lock" or "Steering Column Locked" message appears on the dashboard
the brakes may lock up
and the vehicle may pull to one side.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electronic steering column can cause the vehicle to become inoperable, making it difficult or impossible to start the vehicle, and potentially leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The steering wheel becomes stuck or difficult to turn
the vehicle will not start
the "Service Column Lock" or "Steering Column Locked" message appears on the dashboard
and the brakes may lock up.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the active handling system can cause the vehicle to become unstable, making it difficult to control, and potentially leading to accidents.
symptoms: The "Service Active Handling System" message appears on the dashboard
the brakes may lock up
the vehicle may pull to one side
and the vehicle may become unstable.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission shifter lock can cause the vehicle to become stuck in park, making it difficult or impossible to shift into gear, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle will not shift out of park
the transmission shifter lock is stuck
the vehicle is unable to move
the shifter lever will not move into drive
the vehicle is stuck in park intermittently.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake transmission interlock can cause the vehicle to become stuck in park, making it difficult or impossible to shift into gear, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle will not shift out of park
the brake transmission interlock is stuck
the vehicle is unable to move
the shifter lever will not move into drive
the vehicle is stuck in park intermittently.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the shift solenoid lock can cause the vehicle to become stuck in park, making it difficult or impossible to shift into gear, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle will not shift out of park
the shift solenoid lock is stuck
the vehicle is unable to move
the shifter lever will not move into drive
the vehicle is stuck in park intermittently.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Active Handling System can cause the vehicle to suddenly brake or swerve, leading to loss of control, accidents, or near-misses.
symptoms: The "Service Active Handling" message appears on the dashboard
the brakes lock up or pulse
the vehicle swerves or pulls to one side
the steering wheel becomes difficult to control
and the vehicle may enter "limp mode."

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden loss of headlights while driving at night can cause accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially on dark roads with no streetlights.
symptoms: Low beam headlights suddenly turn off or fail to turn on
often after the engine has warmed up
and may only work intermittently or after the car has cooled down. High beams and fog lights may still function.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause various safety-critical systems to malfunction, including the headlights, brakes, and active handling system, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The "Service Active Handling System" message appears
loss of brake lights
and spontaneous activation of brake lights while driving.
